  "prompt": "How did Oliver Sykes damaged his voice exactly?",
  "response": "Oliver Sykes, the lead vocalist of the band Bring Me the Horizon, has spoken about various challenges he has faced with his voice over the years. He has noted that some of the damage to his vocal cords resulted from improper singing techniques, particularly during the early years of the band's career when he often used a harsh screaming style without adequate vocal training. Additionally, lifestyle factors such as heavy touring, stress, and substance use may have contributed to his vocal issues.\n\nSykes has since taken steps to improve his vocal health, including working with vocal coaches and adopting better techniques for singing and screaming, which has helped him maintain his voice more effectively. He has also discussed his journey to recovery and the importance of taking care of one's vocal health as a singer.",
